parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations, especially when it occurs on a highway.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the engine stalls
the vehicle shuts off while driving
the vehicle hops into neutral without warning
the vehicle slows down or stops unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The uncommanded shift to neutral can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations, especially when it occurs on a highway.
symptoms: The vehicle hops into neutral without warning
the vehicle slows down or stops unexpectedly
the vehicle shifts into neutral while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel pump delivery error can cause the engine to shut off while driving, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: The engine shuts off while driving
the vehicle stalls
the vehicle slows down or stops unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended shift of the transmission into neutral can cause loss of control, especially on wet, icy, or snowy surfaces, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into neutral unexpectedly while driving at low speeds (under 5mph)
slowing
coasting
or during slow accelerations
resulting in a hard shift
loss of traction
and potential loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to Bump or Pothole
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes when driving over a bump or pothole can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to potential accidents or collisions, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The brakes fail to respond when driving over a bump or pothole
the vehicle continues to roll out of control
a loud recoiling sound is heard when the brakes are applied
the emergency brake also fails.
